# statistics_data_smoke.numos — Phase 6D: type a real dataset into StatisticsApp.
#
# Unlike statistics_smoke.numos (which only opens the app on its default empty "Data"
# tab), this script proves StatisticsApp is INTERACTABLE *with real numeric entry*: it
# types the dataset {1, 2, 3} into the value column and switches to the computed "Stats"
# tab, which runs the 1-Var StatsEngine and renders mean/median/.../n over actual data —
# a code path the open-only smoke never reaches.
#
# Phase 6D fixed the digit-entry bug. Previously StatisticsApp detected digits with the
# range test `code >= NUM_0 && code <= NUM_9` (StatisticsApp.cpp), but the KeyCode enum
# declares the digits NON-contiguously and out of order — NUM_7..NUM_9 (row 3),
# NUM_4..NUM_6 (row 4), NUM_1..NUM_3 then NUM_0 last near ENTER (row 5) — so NUM_0 > NUM_9
# and that range was always empty (KeyCodes.h:68-77); every digit key was silently
# ignored. The fix replaces the range test (and the ordering-dependent `code - NUM_0`
# arithmetic) with the explicit, order-independent helper keyCodeDigitValue(KeyCode)
# (KeyCodes.h). Digit keys now register, so a script can set value cells to real numbers.
#
# Data-entry flow (the table starts with exactly ONE row, _numRows=1, StatisticsApp.cpp):
#   * On the Data tab, pressing a digit in nav mode starts an edit and appends the digit
#     (StatisticsApp.cpp default case -> startEdit() + re-process). ENTER commits the
#     value via finishEdit() (atof of the buffer) and returns to nav mode.
#   * AC (nav mode) appends a fresh row (value 0, freq 1, ++_numRows); DOWN moves the
#     focus to it. So the row pattern is: type row 0, then {AC, DOWN, type} per new row.
#   * GRAPH cycles Data -> Stats -> Graph; it is the ONLY key that leaves the Data tab
#     (on Data, LEFT/RIGHT are column nav — the tab-switch guard requires
#     _activeTab != Tab::DATA, StatisticsApp.cpp:521,526). switchTab(STATS) calls
#     recompute() + updateStatsDisplay() over the typed rows. The emulator `key graph`
#     token is mapped in scriptNameToKeyCode (NativeHal.cpp, #ifdef NATIVE_SIM,
#     firmware-neutral).
#   * Over {1,2,3} (each freq 1) recompute() yields n=3, Mean=2, Median=2, Sum=6,
#     Min=1, Max=3. Pure <cmath>/STL StatsEngine: no Giac/CAS, no PSRAM, no LittleFS.
#     Fully deterministic.
#
# As with every emulator screen the only volatile region is the StatusBar clock
# (HH:MM). This phase makes NO golden claim; the screenshot is a CANDIDATE for human
# review only (a clock mask is added by the human at promotion time, rect 4,6,37,13).
#
# Timing notes (deterministic, step-ms 16):
#   * 200 frames -> splash done, in launcher.
#   * 60 frames  -> Statistics screen load + fade settles after open_app.
#   * one frame per key command (1 command/frame).
#   * 120 frames -> Data->Stats tab switch + StatsEngine recompute settles.
#
# Run:
#   program --headless --deterministic --script tests/emulator/scripts/statistics_data_smoke.numos \
#           --frames 800 --screenshot out/statistics_data_smoke.ppm --quiet
# Exit codes: 0 ok · 2 script/parse error · 3 screenshot write error · 4 assertion failure.

log "statistics_data_smoke: waiting for launcher"
wait 200

# Open Statistics (emulator launchApp id 4 — same id as the launcher's Statistics card).
open_app Statistics
wait 60
assert_app Statistics

# Row 0: type value 1 and commit.
key 1
key enter

# Row 1: append a row, move down to it, type value 2 and commit.
key ac
key down
key 2
key enter

# Row 2: append a row, move down to it, type value 3 and commit.
key ac
key down
key 3
key enter

# Switch Data -> Stats: GRAPH is the only key that leaves the Data tab, and it triggers
# recompute() + updateStatsDisplay() over the typed dataset {1,2,3}.
key graph
wait 120

# Screenshot FIRST so the artifact exists even if a later assertion fails.
screenshot out/statistics_data_smoke.ppm
log "statistics_data_smoke: screenshot captured (Stats tab, 1-Var stats over {1,2,3})"

# Still the Statistics app after the in-app tab switch (tab switch does not change g_mode).
assert_app Statistics
log "statistics_data_smoke: assertion passed (Statistics active)"
